WILLIAM HAYTKO, PETITIONER-RESPONDENT, v. WILLIAM CRABB AND CO., RESPONDENT-APPELLANT. Superior Court of New Jersey Appellate Division Argued September 8, 1952 Decided September 16, 1952.

Before Judges Jayne, Peoctob, and Schettino.

Mr. Marshall Crowley argued the cause fox appellant (Messrs. Toner, Crowley •& Aclcerman, attorneys; Mr. Robert A. Vanderbilt, on the brief). Mr. Harry Cohn argued the cause for respondent.

The opinion of the court was delivered

Pee Ctjbiam.

We concur in the conclusion expressed by Judge Erancis and reported in 17 N. J. Super. 95 (Co. Ct., Law Div., 1951).

Affirmed.
